): Palpal tibia with retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) broad at base, gradually narrowing towards its tip when viewed from retrolateral side ( Figs 13 , 17 ); pointing laterally, with anterior margin slightly concave, the apex bearing a small, sharply pointed apical hook, when viewed from ventral ( Figs 11 , 15 ) and dorsal ( Figs 10 , 14 ) sides. Tegulum (T) longer than wide, distal part membranous, basal part sclerotized (
Figs 11 –13
,
15– 17
); sperm duct (SD) one-looped, U-shaped when viewed from ventral side ( Figs 11 , 15 ); subtegulum (ST) strongly sclerotized, elongate oval, clearly visible in prolateral view ( Figs 12 , 16 ). Embolus (E) coiled, originating on top of tegulum, visible as a transverse distal band, filiform embolic tip resting in distal cymbial alveolus ( Figs 11 ,
15– 17
